article.headline: W. Kentucky 73, New Orleans 70
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ky. (AP) -- Courtney Lee made two driving shots in the final minutes to help Western Kentucky hold off New Orleans 73-70 Sunday afternoon. Lee, who had missed the past three games with an ankle injury, gave the Hilltoppers a 71-67 advantage with a left-handed layup and on their next possession made a short running shot with 19.6 seconds to play to give Western Kentucky (15-6, 7-2 Sunbelt Conference) a three-point lead. The Hilltoppers then weathered a missed 3-point attempt from the left corner by the Privateers James Parlow with four seconds to play to claim the victory. New Orleans (9-11, 5-4 SBC) was sparked by Bo McCalebb, who scored a game-high 28 points on 12 of 21 shooting. Tyrone Brazelton led Western Kentucky with 17 points, while Lee added 13 and Jeremy Evans finished with 10. Jamie McNeilly added 17 points for New Orleans, while Shaun Reynolds had 12 and Parlow scored 11.
